A motorcyclist who died following a collision with a car has been named by police. Motorcyclist killed in southside crash named A motorcyclist who died following a collision with a car has been named by police.Alex White, 53, was taken to hospital after the crash on Polmadie Road, on the southside of Glasgow, but died a short time later.The driver of the car was not injured.Police are appealing for information about the collision, which happened at around 5.50am yesterday.Mr White was from the Croftfoot area of Glasgow. 